<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9312.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-24"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Instruct the American consul at Guaymas that he may, in so far as the
                            local authorities may permit him to do so and when such course appears
                            to be necessary, extend informal good offices in behalf of Chinese
                            subjects.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>